meanings.definition: To sell more than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The new bakery hopes to outsell the old one with their delicious pastries.
meanings.sent2: The popular brand always manages to outsell its competitors in the market.
meanings.sent3: The little lemonade stand tried to outsell the big supermarket, but it was a tough challenge.
meanings.sent4: Her determination to outsell her own record was like a runner sprinting towards the finish line.
meanings.sent5: The idea of outselling the giant corporation seemed like a daunting task for the small business owner.

meanings.definition: To be more successful in selling than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The local bookstore aims to outsell the online retailers by offering personalized recommendations.
meanings.sent2: Despite the competition, the talented artist continues to outsell all other painters in the gallery.
meanings.sent3: The idea of a cat trying to outsell a dog in a barking contest is quite amusing.
meanings.sent4: Her determination to outsell her fears was like a warrior facing her enemies head-on.
meanings.sent5: The image of outselling the storm with her bright smile stayed in his memory for years to come.
